# 7. それでも私達は

Minori: H-Haruka, is that true...?!
Minori: We stopped receiving offers because of ReLight...?
Haruka: Yeah. The truth is, I ran into Mr. Hiiragi by accident over at the TV station the other day. I decided to ask him straight out...
Haruka: I'm sorry for not telling you all sooner.
Airi: There's no need for you to apologize. We get that telling us this wasn't easy for you.
Airi: Still, I don't think any of us were expecting this...
Shizuku: But... If what Haruka just said is true, then there was nothing that we could've done.
Haruka: That rumor about Mr. Hiiragi is one thing, and so is the fact that we don't have the backing of a big agency...
Haruka: But the real problem we're facing right now is that we lack the ability to fight back.
Airi: Right... We're in a pretty tough pickle.
Airi: If things end up continuing like this indefinitely...
Minori: Oh no...
Haruka: (Everyone looks so sad...)
Haruka: (But...)
Minori: Then, let's figure out a way!
Minori: Yeah, ReLight is a really amazing idol group... And I admit that I don't stand a chance against them right now...!
Minori: But the last thing we should be doing is feeling bad for ourselves!
Minori: I know that turning this situation around isn't going to be easy, and I have no idea if we'll actually get more work...
Minori: But I don't want us to give up... I want us to take this opportunity to figure out a way to keep our dream of spreading hope to as many people as we can alive!
Haruka: Minori...
Haruka: Hehe. You took the words right out of my mouth.
Minori: Huh?
Haruka: I was actually just about to say the same thing.
Minori: R-Really?! I'm so sorry, Haruka...!
Haruka: Don't apologize. If anything, I'm glad you did.
Haruka: Because now I know that you feel the same way, Minori.
Haruka: We really are in a tough situation right now.
Haruka: But I think I can safely say that we all want to keep spreading hope to others as idols...
Haruka: It's probably going to take us a while to come up with a good plan...
Haruka: But I also want us to figure out a way that allows us to keep spreading hope to others...
Airi: Haruka...
Airi: Yeah... We shouldn't just dwell on our problems here.
Airi: We should be running straight towards our dream instead!
Shizuku: Yes, and... It's times like these when we need to remind ourselves of our ultimate goal.
Shizuku: Let's keep being ourselves, inspire as many people as we can and spread more hope than any other idols out there!
Haruka: Thanks, you two.
Haruka: Then, let's start thinking about how we're going to keep spreading hope to everyone.
Haruka: So, for now, we need to work on raising our standards.
Airi: Right. We were able to punch above our weight during Idol Lovers because we got to perform with ReLight...
Airi: We have to learn how to consistently perform like that—no, even better than we did that time—if we want people to invite us to their events.
Shizuku: Then, why don't we start by overhauling our workout routines?
Haruka: Agreed. We all excel at different things as performers, so it might be good for each of us to train with our different strengths in mind.
Haruka: I'll come up with some new exercises for all of you.
Minori: Thanks, Haruka!
Haruka: Also, we've been relying mostly on Saito to find work for us, but I'll start being more active in that department.
Airi: Right. I'll try asking around as well.
Minori: Then, while you guys do that, I'll come up with stream ideas for us!
Haruka: Thanks. Oh, speaking of which, we may also need to start rethinking our streams a bit...
Haruka: As important as it is to think about our existing viewers, we have to start thinking about how we're going to get more people to start watching us.
Haruka: This seems like a good list of ideas for now.
Airi: Yeah... But to be perfectly honest, none of them seem like a definitive solution to get us back on our feet.
Shizuku: Still, it's better than doing nothing at all.
Haruka: I agree. This is going to be a process of trial and error. We'll try the things we talked about today, see what works and what doesn't and try to make progress bit by bit.
Minori: Yeah...! So, let's do everything we can for now!
Haruka: (I do agree with Airi... None of these feel like they'll lead to the breakthrough we need.)
Haruka: (But we have to keep moving forward.)
Haruka: (We have to believe that we'll get out of this jam and keep spreading hope to others...!)
Haruka: (No luck again today...)
Haruka: (Saito, Airi and I have been asking around a lot, but... It's been really rough.)
Haruka: (I mean, people are rejecting us outright. Very few have been willing to even hear us out.)
Haruka: (I knew this wouldn't be easy. If this isn't working, we just need to try something else.)
Haruka: (We just have to keep trying everything we can right now.)
Haruka: Alright, the others are currently practicing, so I should get changed and go work out...
Haruka: A visitor? But we're not scheduled to meet anyone today...
Haruka: Who could it be? Wait, huh...?
Haruka: Ms. Arisawa...?
Landlady: Hello. Do you have a minute?
